		"body": "## Summary\r\n- Restore legacy macOS close behavior by hiding the app (not just the main window) when the main window is closed without quitting.\r\n- Add a shared main-window restore path and call it from both `activate` and `did-become-active` so Cmd+Tab reliably re-shows the main window.\r\n- Fixes #14169 where Joplin can stay windowless after `Cmd+W` then app switching.\r\n\r\n## Test plan\r\n- [x] On macOS, launch desktop app and confirm main window is visible.\r\n- [x] Press `Cmd+W` to close the main window while keeping app running.\r\n- [x] Switch away with `Cmd+Tab`, then switch back to Joplin with `Cmd+Tab`.\r\n- [x] Confirm the main window is restored and focused.\r\n- [x] Repeat the close/switch cycle 2-3 times to verify consistency.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
