			"body": "<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: summarize by coderabbit.ai -->\n<!-- walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>📝 Walkthrough</summary>\n\n## Walkthrough\n\nA refactoring that centralises main window display logic into a new private `showMainWindow_()` helper method, with Darwin-specific handling and window restoration, replacing direct show/focus calls across multiple lifecycle event handlers.\n\n## Changes\n\n|Cohort / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**Main Window Display Logic Consolidation** <br> `packages/app-desktop/ElectronAppWrapper.ts`|Introduces private `showMainWindow_()` helper to centralise window show/restore/focus operations with platform-specific macOS handling. Refactors lifecycle event handlers (window close, app activation, did-become-active) to route window display through this single method instead of direct calls.|\n\n## Suggested labels\n\n`desktop`, `macOS`, `bug`\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 5</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ Passed checks (5 passed)</summary>\n\n|         Check name         | Status   | Explanation                                                                                                                                                                                          |\n| :------------------------: | :------- | :--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|         Title check        | ✅ Passed | The title accurately summarizes the main change: restoring macOS window on app re-activation after close, which directly addresses the core fix in the changeset.                                    |\n|      Description check     | ✅ Passed | The description is clearly related to the changeset, explaining the legacy behaviour restoration an